<br>
Barbarians are the better trade off.  Welcome in all cities save the evil ones.  Have innate bash/slam without the need to have a shield.  They don't have it as well as ogres who can Bash right off the bat.  Barbarians have a good starting zone however.  Many more mobs, yer closer to better areas than the other primary warrior starting points.  Yer close to black burrow tho, which is very good exp.  The biggest draw back is not seeing in the dark all that well.  Easily remedy however, many items can be put in inventory to allow better vision.  Many weapons are very good light sources, Axe of the Iron Back and the runic carver come to mind.  A gnome skin mask and gnoll hide mask are also decent light source when worn.  I use a macro slot where I have put an empty inventory slot, and the face slot for changing on the fly when a mask offers more ac etc.  Currentlly using an Antlered mask durring combat and gnome skin in low light situations when ultra or serpent is not available.<br>
<br>
Personally I like my barbarian, I know they may seem to be a dime a dozen but they work really well as a warrior.  Not to big in relation to ogres and trolls, but nor do they lack the ability to bash using dual weild.  Have a good CR too, and velious is mucho cold spells, not sure if many give this much consioderation at lower levels but when you need the resist later in life its nice to have some.  Ogres have a good heat resist too tho.<br>
<br>
Its all about what ya want really....personally a one eyed barbarian seems tae have a way wit they ladies 'O da realm!  <br>
<br>
Luck to ya. <p>Bearog Frostborne
Warrior 45th Turning</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ujarren01.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jarren01</A></span><br> <b>knows that Warriors are Superior</b><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/19/01 9:09:24 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.best.com/~sjshark/newsig.JPG height=137 width=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Getting started</span><hr size=1> I personally picked a half elf warrior to be my ALT...and have never regretted it.  It's nice to be able to run around dungeons and not have to worry about getting a shrink.  The lack of the slam ability can be an issue but considering I play a bard as main, I'm used to swapping weapons/instruments on the go and hence ghetto bashing is an acceptable alternative.<br>
